caption: Would be 0 stars.  Came here to watch 10 MD vs 7 UCONN.  Got setup in a great spot with two TVs with the game on.  5 mins before the end of the first half, both get changed to Hockey...intermission reports...I’m a fan of Hockey but how does a sports bar, ruin March madness, for the Intermission report of mid-season hockey.  Awful.  Next time gonna grab a case and watch at home.  Glad they finally got it back on just in time for half time.  Seriously you can’t make this nonsense up.  (Good on the Owner!  Thank you for the free round.  It’s a small gesture but greatly appreciated.  Thanks for understanding some folks never see their teams in this tournament or haven’t in awhile.  And to diehards like me it’s a big deal, the pride you feel for your team or State.  Thank you, adjusted stars.)

I bought a soda for my friend who doesn't drink. I figured they charged for each soda he got, because they charged me for two, but my friend only had one soda. I wish this is the worst thing I could say about the bar. We ordered a burger, nachos, wings, and mozzarella sticks. The mozzarella sticks were served with salsa instead of marinara and the cheese was melted for all of 10 minutes. I had to order the mozzarella sticks twice to get them too. The nachos were served with radishes, but otherwise they were ok if Taco Bell quality. The wings were cold, neon colored red, and the sauce tasted awful. The burgers bun was stale, and the burger was overcooked and crumbling. Overall I would not recommend going here for even drinks.
